Class Event

java.lang.Object
Event
Direct Known Subclasses:
ArriveEvent, DoneEvent, LeaveEvent, ServeEvent, WaitEvent
public abstract class Event extends Object
The abstract Event class provides some concrete methods and specifies some abstract methods to be implemented by all inheriting child classes. Primarily, each Event will contain a timeStamp that indicates the time at which said event occurs, a Customer associated with the event, and a server associated with the event.

Events that do not require a server are assigned a dummy server to facilitate substitutability and polymorphic behaviour.

    • nextEvent

      protected abstract Pair<Event,ImList<Server>> nextEvent(ImList<Server> inputList)
      Abstract method specification for generating the next event. All classes that inherit from Event are required to implement this method. Returns a Pair<Event, ImList<Server>> containing the next event as its first item and the updated list of servers returned after processing the next event as its second item.
      Parameters:
      inputList - An ImList<Server> of servers for processing next Event
      Returns:
      A Pair<Event, ImList<Server>> pair
